  "original_title": "\u0d85\u0da9\u0dd4 \u0da7\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca\u0da9\u0dbb\u0dba \u0d85\u0dc4\u0ddd\u0dc3\u0dd2 \u0d9a\u0dbb \u0dc0\u0dd0\u0da9\u0dd2 \u0db8\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0da7 \u0d9c\u0dd1\u0dc3\u0dca \u0d85\u0dbb\u0db1\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Canceled the low tender and bought gas at a higher price",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Term Tender, which had been approved by the Cabinet to buy gas at a low price, was canceled c. Mr. Charita Herath, Chairman of the Parliamentary Committee on Public Enterprises (COPE Committee) recommended that an investigation be conducted through the Auditor General's Department regarding the purchase of 100,000 MT of gas at a higher price of USD 129 each.",
        "Also, the COPE committee has recommended to immediately look into the inability to purchase gas with the amount of 160 million USD allocated to purchase gas under the Indian credit facility.",
        "Yesterday, their heads were summoned before the CORP committee to inquire how the orders given by the committee, Litro Gas Lanka Company, Litro Gas Terminal Lanka (Pvt) Company and Sri Lanka Insurance Corporation were implemented and the performance of those institutions. These recommendations were given in that meeting.",
        "It was revealed that since the seasonal tender for the purchase of gas ended by last February, tenders were invited to purchase 2,80,000 mt of gas and accordingly, three gas suppliers submitted bids. Here, Siam Gas Company has submitted the lowest price as USD 96 and accordingly the Cabinet has approved to award the tender."
      ],
